'''''Mission Asteroid''''' (shown as '''''Mission: Asteroid''''' in the manual and on the title screen)<ref name=mania/> is a [[graphic adventure]] game for the [[Apple II series|Apple II]] written by Ken and Roberta Williams and released in 1980 by [[Sierra Entertainment|On-Line Systems]].<ref name="giantlist"/>

==Publication history==
The game was released as ''[[List of Hi-Res Adventures video games|Hi-Res Adventures]]'' #0, despite being released after ''[[Mystery House]]'' and ''[[Wizard and the Princess]]''. It was meant as an introduction to the adventure game genre so it was made easier than the rest of ''Hi-Res Adventures'' games.<ref name="cat81">{{cite web | title=On-Line Systems Catalog | url=https://www.sierragamers.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Catalog_1981_On_Line_Systems.pdf | date=1981}}</ref>

It was ported to the [[Atari 8-bit computers]]<ref name="mania"/> and [[Commodore 64]].

==Reception==
[[File:On-Line Systems - Hi-Res Adventure - June 1981 The On-Line Letter advert.jpg|thumb|left|Advertisement from the June 1981 issue of ''The On-Line Letter'' for some of On-Line Systems' ''Hi-Res Adventure'' games, including ''Mission Asteroid''.]]
Mark Marlow reviewed ''Mission: Asteroid'', ''Mystery House'', and ''The Wizard and the Princess'' for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Mission: Asteroid'' is the simplest of the group and only requires a few hours to solve".<ref name="CGW2">{{cite magazine | last=Marlow | first=Mark | title=Micro - Reviews | magazine=Computer Gaming World | date=January–February 1982 | volume=1 | issue=2 | pages=31–32}}</ref>

